features.name: RusA Endonuclease that resolves Holliday junction intermediates made during homologous genetic recombination and DNA repair. Exhibits sequence and structure-selective cleavage of four-way DNA junctions, where it introduces symmetrical nicks in two strands of the same polarity at the 5' side of dinucleotides. Corrects the defects in genetic recombination and DNA repair associated with inactivation of ruvAB or ruvC
Phage_connect_1 Phage gp6-like head-tail connector protein
Phage_TAC_7 Phage tail assembly chaperone proteins, E, or 41 or 14
Caudo_TAP Caudovirales tail fibre assembly protein, lambda gpK
SecIII_SopE_N,SopE_GEF guanine nucleotide exchange factor (GEF). This activation results in actin cytoskeleton rearrangements and stimulates membrane ruffling
